OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax     F353A1733314321
OL,3,CHospice bosses battle against rising
OL,4,Ccosts and drop in donations
OL,6,F"We get a small amount of our money
OL,7,Ffrom the government through the NHS.
OL,8,FSo for us that's about 20%. The other
OL,9,F80% we rely upon our community."
OL,11,FWith challenges making it harder for
OL,12,Fhospices to operate, Ms Clayton is
OL,13,Fcalling for a change to how hospices
OL,14,Fare funded, with more support coming
OL,15,Ffrom the government.
OL,17,FMs Clayton thinks it is problematic
OL,18,Fthat doctors who are experts in
OL,19,Fpalliative care are paid for largely
OL,20,Fby donations, whereas a doctor in the
OL,21,FNHS is funded by the NHS.
OL,1,W{$~k4{$k4~sjw=                 G3/6
